Source: Player's Handbook

//Evocation cantrip//

**Casting Time:** 1 action
**Range:** 120 feet
**Components:** V, S
**Duration:** Instantaneous

You launch a smoky streak of black energy toward a creature within range. Make a ranged spell attack against the target. On a hit, the target takes 1d4 necrotic damage. You recover half of the total damage as hit points.

**//Shadowy Strength.//** When moving through darkness, the spell can cling to the shadows to move. The range of this spell can be increased by up to 15 feet when it is moving through darkness. [[footnote]]Specifically, the spell can take a free 15 feet of additional range, so long as that 15 feet is through darkness. You don't automatically get the 15 feet just by standing in the dark, or shooting it through a shadow. The additional range directly corresponds to the amount of darkness the spell travels through.[[/footnote]]

**//At Higher Levels.//** The spell creates more than one beam when you reach higher levels: two beams at 5th level, three beams at 11th level, and four beams at 17th level. You can direct the beams at the same target or at different ones. Make a separate attack roll for each beam.

